    {
      "id": "cab0e200_e187f69e",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "Per our discussion in the Monday meeting, we should make it clear that this is INTENT of the PTL, rather than the current state.  IOW - if the current state is ACTIVE, but the PTL intends for it to be UNMAINTAINED, then this would be set to true.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6161,
        "name": "David McBride",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dmcbride@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "dmcbride"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-23 16:26:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "2ec35747_3178d55c",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "See comment for \"unamaintained\" above.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6161,
        "name": "David McBride",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dmcbride@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "dmcbride"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-23 16:26:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "18527f25_bd91f216",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "This field might be more clear if re-named \"request_unmaintained\" or similar.  Less likely to confuse current state with intent of the ptl.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6161,
        "name": "David McBride",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dmcbride@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "dmcbride"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-23 19:08:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "db8f0663_3390c0f1",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "This field might be more clear if re-named \"request_read_only\" or similar.  Less likely to confuse current state with intent of the ptl.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6161,
        "name": "David McBride",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dmcbride@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "dmcbride"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-23 19:08:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8e5fabc8_532b28d1",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "We really have three states that need to be conveyed:\n\nunmaintained -- ones that are ALREADY in unmaintained state and there's no request pending to make them unmaintained\n\nrequest_unmaintained -- (using your term) these are ones that the PTLs want to move into unmaintained state as part of the current release\n\nconfirmed_request_unmaintained -- (need another term) these are the ones that the PTLs want to move into unmaintained as part of the current release and we have agreement that they should be listed as unmaintained. This is really a sub-state of \"request_unmaintained\", so could be another parameter like \"confirmed\" that is only used with \"request_unmaintained\"\n\nAt the END of the release, before cutting the branch named for the release from the master, all \"request_unmaintained\" that are \"confirmed\" become \"unmaintained\" and all of the rest of the \"request_unmaintained\" ones go back to maintained status.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 105,
        "name": "Tony Hansen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tony@att.com",
        "username": "TonyLHansen"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-24 12:04:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "18527f25_bd91f216",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "af3ccb83_5b33f6dd",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "See my comment above. The same three states apply here as well.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 105,
        "name": "Tony Hansen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tony@att.com",
        "username": "TonyLHansen"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-24 12:04:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "db8f0663_3390c0f1",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bead22bd_3005f9a1",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "This seems way too complicated. A year or two after this is implemented, everyone will forget what these terms mean and things will be as confused as they are now, or more.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6161,
        "name": "David McBride",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dmcbride@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "dmcbride"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-24 16:49:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8e5fabc8_532b28d1",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "628a7853_50d4c344",
      "file_path": "repos/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "thinking further on this, perhaps the answer is to use a single name unmaintained with three possible values: true, false, and requested",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 105,
        "name": "Tony Hansen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tony@att.com",
        "username": "TonyLHansen"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-24 18:53:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8e5fabc8_532b28d1",
      "unresolved": true
    },
